    <segment id="1" parent="3" relname="span">According to Dictionary.com, intuitiveness is of, relating to, or arising from intuition; known or perceived through intuition; possessing or demonstrating intuition. </segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="1" relname="elaboration">
Intuition is knowledge gained by the use of this faculty; a perceptive insight.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="22" relname="span"> 
Another word for intuitiveness is innate knowledge. </segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="23" relname="span">
Innate knowledge is like knowing right from wrong. </segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="5" relname="elaboration">
You just KNOW that it is wrong to push someone. </segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="18" relname="circumstance">
In regards to program design, when you use it</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="27" relname="span"> you should be able to just operate it without having to go through some type of tutorial every time. </segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="25" relname="span">
For example, when you use email. </segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="10" relname="concession">
Even though there are many different user interfaces </segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="17" relname="span">
it is all the same (generally speaking). </segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="10" relname="elaboration">
You know that there is going to be a way to reply, forward, delete, view the next email, view the previous email, etc. </segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="19" relname="solutionhood">
How do you measure intuitiveness? </segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="19" relname="list">
You can measure it by the amount of times that a user has to refer to the Help section after using the system 5 times. </segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="26" relname="span">
You can test the user on different features of the system. </segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="20" relname="circumstance">
For example, when you apply for a job</segment>
    <segment id="20" parent="21" relname="span"> and they make you take a test that will see how well you use Microsoft Excel. </segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="20" relname="elaboration">
According how many you get wrong will determine how much of an expert you really are.</segment>
